HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 734
By Vital
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Burl Lee Herron of
Georgetown.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Burl Lee Herron; and
WHEREAS, Burl Herron was a beloved friend and neighbor who did his utmost to
improve the well-being of all who were blessed to know him; and
WHEREAS, born on July 8, 1947, in Georgetown, Mr. Herron was the son of Willie Paul
Herron and Mildred Louise Fornter Herron; and
WHEREAS, Burl Herron served as captain of the Highway 58 Fire Department Station 3,
in which position he earned the respect and admiration of his colleagues and a grateful public;
and
WHEREAS, a man of many passions, Mr. Herron owned a dairy farm and his own
excavation company for more than thirty years; and
WHEREAS, Burl Herron was a devoted member of Birchwood Church of God of
Prophecy; and
WHEREAS, he was also deeply devoted to his family and always endeavored to remain
true to family values of the highest order; and
WHEREAS, he is survived by his wife of fifty-six years, Stella Herron; his son, Kendall
(Chandra) Herron; his grandchildren, Kayla Herron, MaKinley Herron, and Tucker Herron; and a
host of nieces, nephews, cousins, and friends; and
WHEREAS, in addition to his parents, Mr. Herron was preceded in death by his sister,
Doris Carroll; and
HJR0734
010833
- 1 -

WHEREAS, throughout his many worthy endeavors, Burl Herron distinguished himself
as a beacon of kindness and wisdom; and
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should pay tribute to the bountiful life of this exceptional
Tennessean; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor the memory of Burl Lee Herron, reflecting fondly upon his ability
to live the examined life with courage and conviction.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we extend our sympathy and condolences to the
family and friends of Mr. Herron.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
